ЁЯТ╗ Run Locally on Your Own PC
If you want to run it on your own computer for development:
Prerequisites:
Node.js (version 18+)
Git
A code editor (VS Code recommended)
Steps:
Download the source code (I provided the complete source in the previous message)
Extract the files to a folder on your PC
Open terminal/command prompt in that folder
Install dependencies:
bash
cd backend
npm install
cd ../frontend
npm install
Start the servers:
bash
# Terminal 1 - Backend
cd backend
npm start

# Terminal 2 - Frontend  
cd frontend
npm run dev
Open browser to http://localhost:5173
